echo Uses: You if you wish to globally add a command to pycmd, add it to:\n{cwd}/pcmd\nThe extension must be pcmd.\n\nTo run code, simply type pcmd or pycmd in the terminal and then the name of that file.\n\n.pcmd files run through the terminal in the same way that entering commands does, therefore, pcmd files should be written as if you were in the command prompt with && or newlines seperating each command.
